annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L28; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; neurogenesis; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL28 family
annotationB: 40S ribosomal protein S18; Located at the top of the head of the 40S subunit, it contacts several helices of the 18S rRNA
